1 Sec. 6. 29-A MRSA §851, sub-§2-A is enacted to read:
2 2-A. Electronic temporary registration plate program. "Electronic temporary
3 registration plate program" means an electronic program that permits the creation of a
4 temporary registration plate and the maintenance of temporary registration plate
5 information.
6 Sec. 7. 29-A MRSA §954-A, sub-§1-A is enacted to read:
7 1-A. Electronic temporary registration plate program. Notwithstanding any
8 provision of law to the contrary, the Secretary of State may use, but may not require the
9 use of, an electronic temporary registration plate program. If the Secretary of State uses an
10 electronic temporary registration plate program under this subsection, the Secretary of State
11 may adopt rules to implement and administer the program. Rules adopted under this
12 subsection must include, but are not limited to, rules governing the process by which a
13 dealer elects to participate in or stop participating in the electronic temporary registration
14 plate program. Rules adopted under this subsection are routine technical rules as defined
15 in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
16 Sec. 8. 29-A MRSA §954-A, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2021, c. 126, §1 and
17 reallocated by PL 2023, c. 257, §7, is further amended to read:
18 2. Payment of fee for temporary registration plate. The fee for a temporary
19 registration plate is $1 $2.00 per plate, $1.00 of which must be deposited into the Motor
20 Vehicle Services Fund established under section 159 to establish and maintain an electronic
21 temporary registration plate program. A purchaser may operate the motor vehicle or trailer
22 with a temporary registration plate for a period of 30 consecutive days without payment of
23 a regular fee. At the end of this initial period, a resident who is unable to comply with the
24 requirements of chapter 7 or a nonresident who has applied for but has not yet received a
25 registration certificate from a home state may request the Secretary of State to extend this
26 period without charge for an additional 20 days.
27 Sec. 9. Effective date. That section of this Act that enacts the Maine Revised
28 Statutes, Title 29-A, section 651-A, subsection 4 and that section that amends Title 29-A,
29 section 954-A, subsection 2 take effect January 1, 2026.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This bill allows the Secretary of State to adopt rules to administer self-service kiosks
3322 for vehicle registration renewals and driver's license and nondriver identification card
3333 renewals and replacements. It imposes a $1.00 fee on electronic lien titling transactions.
34 The bill clarifies that the process to dispose of vehicle parts is in the same manner as
35 for the entire vehicle. It clarifies that impounded vehicles and vehicle parts are the property
36 of the Secretary of State. It requires an owner or lienholder claiming ownership of a vehicle
37 or vehicle part to take possession within 30 days from receipt of notice. It allows the
38 Secretary of State to dispose of a vehicle or vehicle part in a manner considered appropriate
39 and requires any proceeds from a sale to be deposited in the Motor Vehicle Services Fund.
40 The bill also defines the term "electronic temporary registration plate program" and
41 enables the Secretary of State to establish an electronic temporary registration plate
42 program and adopt rules to administer the program. It also increases the temporary
Page 2 - 132LR0515(01)

413 registration plate fee by $1.00 to support the electronic temporary registration plate
424 program.
